latestPosts.caption:
I promised I’d be better at documenting my food & nutrition. So here’s my first attempt. Made this on father’s day, super easy, relatively healthy, and delicious. 

Sauce:
1/2 cup white wine
1 tsp dried oregano
1/2 tsp salt
1/2 tsp paprika

Chicken thigh marinate:
1 pound chicken thigh (I use licious)
Salt & Pepper
1 tsp oregano
1 tsp parika

Method:
1. Add 1/2 tsp of olive oil to the skillet
2. Add chopped onions (wing the amount)
3. Add spinach (2 cups - it shrinks like mad!), paprika, salt and pepper 
4. In a separate bowl - mix cheese/vegan cheese (violife brand) with chopped garlic, salt, and pepper
5. Take the spinach & onion off the heat and chop it up
6. Mix the spinach and onion mix along with the cheese mix in one bowl
7. Pat dry the chicken thighs and season with oregaon, salt, pepper, and paprika on both sides. 
8. Place the chicken thighs in a baking dish9.  Place 2 tbsp of the spinach and cheese mixture in the middle of each chicken thigh and use a tooth pick to keep it together
9. Make the sauce (ingredients mentioned)
10. Spoon the sauce over the chicken
11. Cover the chicken with foil and bake for 15 mins @ 220 c
12. If you feel like making the chicken cheesier, add some grated cheese for 5 mins before pulling the chicken out
13. Serve with love ❤️

latestPosts.caption:
Been reflecting on the journey so far...

There’s a reason I picked the song ‘Praise You.’ While it’s amazing to see Kica become what it is today, what means more is the personal growth it’s given me.

I started at 25, and 8.5 years later, this journey has taught me so much — it’s raised me, humbled me, and shaped habits I really value today.

Being a founder can be lonely. There’s self-doubt, sleepless nights, work that goes unseen — and through it all, I’ve felt the full spectrum of emotions: the highs, the lows, the wins, the burnout, the pride, and everything in between. But you keep showing up, stay hopeful, and do your best to manifest the luck and success you dream of.

Success looks different for everyone, but for me, it’s been building something I love — with the support of people who’ve been there through it all.

A kica chica for life 🫶🏽

Consistency hopefully will get me there.. and @adito_sen & @meenakshikanoongo pushing me relentlessly ✊🏾🫶🏽 and @kicaactive for always making me feel 💯
